Happy ##worldradioday!
üéô
Radio is a powerful medium for celebrating humanity in all its diversity and constitutes a platform for democratic discourse. At the global level, radio remains the most widely consumed medium. This unique ability to reach out the widest audience means radio can shape a society‚Äôs experience of diversity, stand as an arena for all voices to speak out, be represented and heard. Radio stations should serve diverse communities, offering a wide variety of programs, viewpoints and content, and reflect the diversity of audiences in their organizations and operations.
üéô
On World Radio Day 2020 (WRD 2020), @unesco calls on radio stations to uphold diversity, both in their newsroom and on the airwaves.
This edition of WRD is divided into three main sub-themes:
Advocating for pluralism in radio, including a mix of public, private and community broadcasters;
Encouraging representation in the newsroom, with teams comprised of diverse society groups;
Promoting a diversity of editorial content and programme types reflecting the variety of the audiences.

Arthur Fleck turning into Joker is a defeat or an evolution?
Joaquin Phoenix is the absolute protagonist of Joker by Todd Philips. In the origin story of Batman's principal antagonist, Phoenix portrays Arthur Fleck who, in a world that lacks empathy, can‚Äôt find his place in despite putting always on his ‚Äúhappy face‚Äù. Phoenix reveals to @fatachiari how he preferred to be Joker rather than Arthur Fleck as the former is constantly defeated by rules and constrictions while the latter is finally free to be whoever he wants: dancing, laughing out loud.
With his incredible performance in @jokermovie , Joaquin Phoenix is the favorite possible winner for Best Actor in a Leading Role at the 92nd Academy Awards.
Will he outperform the competition of the other nominated actors: #leonardodicaprio, #antoniobanderas, #adamdriver, #jonathanpryce?
Waiting to find it out, watch the interview with Joaquin..link in bio and on IGTV!

From Diane, the mysterious character who supports Agent Cooper, the main character of Twin Peaks; Renata Klein, the true essence of the self-made woman in Big Little Lies; to Nora Fanshaw the wife‚Äôs lawyer in @marriagestory. 
In this film, Baumbach gifts her with one of the best speeches/lines in cinema so far. Laura‚Äôs presence through her character is a statement that women can have it all or at least can try to achieve this completion.
Laura is nominated for Best Supporting Actress at the 92nd Academy Awards.
Listen to her interview...link in bio!

With her two nominations for @theacademy awards (Best Actress in a leading role for @marriagestory and Best Actress in a supporting role for @jojorabbitmovie ), this is the season of #scarlettjohansson . 
In #MarriageStory, directed by #NoahBaumbach, she is Nicole, a former teen film actress that faces the tragedy of the breaking up of the marriage trying, at the same time, to protect the unity of the family.
In #jojorabbit directed by #taikawaititi , Scarlett plays Rosie, an irreducible anti-nazi mother that tries to convince her young son Jojo to believe that positivity and optimism are the best ways to be free of oppression.
Will Scarlett win an #oscar (or maybe two)?
What do you think of her performances in these two films?
Check the link in bio for more insights about Jojo Rabbit and Marriage Story, and listen to our interview with Scarlett!

Nonni stravaganti, amici sull‚Äôorlo di una crisi di nervi e improbabili baby-sitter non saranno loro di aiuto.
Tra attimi di felicit√† e situazioni di sconforto, Sara e Nicola riusciranno a resistere e a rimanere insieme?
1+1 fa 11 e non 2 quando si parla di figli, lo scrive #MattiaTorre, lo dirige #GiuseppeBonito e lo recitano Valerio Mastandrea e Paola Cortellesi in #Figli, nelle sale italiane in questi giorni. Non solo il racconto di una coppia alle prese con la nascita del secondo figlio in un‚ÄôItalia dove tutti odiano tutti e non c‚Äô√® posto per i 30-40enni ma il racconto di una generazione a cui sono rimaste le briciole e l‚Äôottimismo diventa una scelta. Mattia Torre negli ultimi mesi di vita aveva affidato le redini del progetto a Giuseppe Bonito che lo ha portato avanti egregiamente. Valerio Mastandrea e Paola Cortellesi parlano alla nostra @fatachiari di figli, di famiglia, di cambiare i modelli culturali dominanti della nostra societ√† ma soprattutto raccontano la responsabilit√† di portare sullo schermo il genio di Torre, la sua essenza.

Fresh from Harvard Law School, fledgling attorney Bryan Stevenson (Michael B. Jordan) defies the wishes of his parents, who are concerned about the notoriously racist South, when he ventures to Alabama to open a law practice to support death row inmates routinely denied proper legal counsel. Meeting with a variety of prisoners, Stevenson soon encounters Walter ‚ÄúJohnny D‚Äù McMillan ( @iamjamiefoxx ), a black man accused of the brutal murder of a white teenage girl, an allegation he vehemently denies, with numerous factors clearly supporting innocence. Despite Johnny D‚Äôs skepticism that he will be afforded due diligence by a corrupt system, Stevenson hires local advocate Eva Ansley ( @brielarson), and mounts an urgent case for a retrial, uncovering a chain of injustices and crucial oversights as they search for the truth. Adapted from Bryan Stevenson‚Äôs own bestselling memoir, director Destin Daniel Cretton‚Äôs methodical and interrogative approach paints a searing (and often infuriating) portrait of the fight for justice in the face of structural racism, which feels all-too timely nearly three decades after the case in question. Driven by powerhouse performances from Jordan and Foxx, who are ably supported by a stellar cast including Larson, Rafe Spall, and O‚ÄôShea Jackson Jr, this is cinema at its most inspiring and essential.
.
@mattmicucci interviews @michaelbjordan , actor of the film @justmercyfilm.
Jordan provides to us with a short introduction to Stevenson from his perspective, having lived ‚Äúin his skin‚Äù for this movie, and answers whether he sees the role of the actor as an artist whose duty, in the words of Nina Simone, is to reflect the times.

Inspired by true events, Seberg tells the story of √Ä bout de souffle (Breathless) star and darling of the French New Wave, Jean Seberg, who in the late 1960s was targeted by the illegal FBI surveillance program COINTELPRO. Seberg‚Äôs political and romantic involvement with civil rights activist Hakim Jamal made her a target of the FBI‚Äôs ruthless attempts to disrupt, discredit and expose the Black Power movement. An ambitious young FBI agent, Jack Solomon, is assigned to surveil her, only to find his fate dangerously interwoven with her own.
Chiara Nicoletti and David Martos met the director Benedict Andrews and the actress Kristen Stewart who talk about the realization of the film, and their love for Jean Seberg. Quoting Andrews and Stewart‚Äôs own words: ‚ÄúThis film is a love letter to Jean Seberg so that people can finally see her for the brave woman she was and not only for her fragility and that famous haircut of hers‚Äù.

E dopo una parentesi imprevedibile quanto misteriosa, il Segretario di Stato Voiello riesce nell‚Äôimpresa di far salire al soglio pontificio Sir John Brannox, un aristocratico inglese moderato, affascinante e sofisticato che prende il nome di Giovanni Paolo III. E capisce subito che sar√† difficile prendere il posto del carismatico Pio XIII: sospeso tra la vita e la morte Lenny Belardo √® diventato un Santo.

Torna il papa interpretato da Jude Law, questa volta affiancato da John Malkovich in The New Pope, la nuova serie di Paolo Sorrentino che si lega a The Young Pope Italia e sar√† in onda su Sky Atlantic Italia dal 10 gennaio.
